						<summary>

						<p>On the east wall of the <hi rend="italic">maṇḍapa</hi> infront of the central shrine, Bhaktajanēśvara temple (right of entrance).</p>						

						<p><hi rend="bold">Year 16: 987 A.D.</hi></p>						

						<p>Records a gift of a gold plate <hi rend="italic">(paṭṭam)</hi> weighing six <hi rend="italic">kaḻañju</hi> and ten <hi rend="italic">mā</hi> to the god Tiruttoṇḍīśvarattu Mahādēva at Tirunāvalūr in Tirumuṉaippāḍi by the official who took down the orders of the king <hi rend="italic">(uḍaiyār mandira-ōlai eḻudum)</hi> Taṉḍikaṉ Chēraṉ <hi rend="italic">alias</hi> Kuṭṭippaṭṭaṉ of Vakkāṉpākkam. </p>						

